                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Dark Factory -->
        <section id="dark-factory" class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">Dark Factory</span>
                <h2>Your factory runs in the dark.<br /><em>RuneFort turns the lights on.</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    Autonomous software factories &mdash; spec in, tested code out, no human in the loop &mdash;
                    are real and shipping production code today. The question is no longer
                    &ldquo;can agents build software?&rdquo; but &ldquo;can you see what they're doing?&rdquo;
                </p>

                <!-- Maturity strip -->
                <div class="maturity-strip">
                    <div class="maturity-level">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L0</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Manual</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">Human writes everything</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="maturity-level">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L1</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Delegation</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">AI handles discrete tasks</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="maturity-level">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L2</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Pairing</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">AI copilot, human drives</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="maturity-level">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L3</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Review</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">AI writes, human reviews</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="maturity-level active">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L4</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Spec-Driven</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">Specs in, code out</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="maturity-level active">
                        <div class="maturity-num">L5</div>
                        <div class="maturity-title">Dark Factory</div>
                        <div class="maturity-desc">Fully autonomous</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="dark-factory-split">
                    <div class="df-card dark">
                        <h3>The dark factory</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Specs go in, tested software comes out</li>
                            <li>No human writes or reviews code</li>
                            <li>Holdout validation separates train/test</li>
                            <li>Graph-structured agent pipelines</li>
                            <li>Digital twin universes for integration</li>
                            <li>Production code shipping today</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="df-card lit">
                        <h3>RuneFort adds</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бҡІ</span> Spatial observability &mdash; walk through the pipeline</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣҸ</span> Governance walls &mdash; Delegatic policy enforcement</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣү</span> Diagnostic watchtowers &mdash; PRISM anomaly detection</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бҡ·</span> Bridge visibility &mdash; see tokens cross system boundaries</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бҡ№</span> Trust scoring &mdash; FleetPrompt reputation on every agent</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣғ</span> Learning feedback &mdash; the fort improves with every cycle</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- B2B visual -->
                <div class="b2b-visual">
                    <pre>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ңв”Җ Your Fort в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ңв”Җ Partner Fort в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”ҖRetrieveв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”ҖRouteв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”Ҹв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”“  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ бҡІ nodes  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ бҡЁ Оә=0  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”ғ              в”ғ  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”ғ   в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘   в”ғ  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”ҖActв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”ҖLearnв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ</span> <span class="bridge">в•җв•җв•җ</span><span class="token">бҡ·</span><span class="bridge">в•җв•җв•җ</span> <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”ғ   opaque     в”ғ  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ бҡ  store  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ бӣғ feed в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”ғ              в”ғ  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в”Ӯ  в”—в”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”Ғв”ӣ  в”Ӯ</span>
<span class="your-fort">в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ</span>       <span class="partner-fort">в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ</span>
   <span class="your-fort">full visibility</span>               <span class="bridge">bridge</span>        <span class="partner-fort">walls + gates only</span></pre>
                </div>
                <p style="color: var(--dim); font-size: 0.88rem; max-width: 700px;">
                    <strong style="color: var(--text);">B2B privacy boundary:</strong>
                    You see full detail inside your own fort. Partner forts appear as opaque shapes &mdash;
                    outer walls, gates, and bridge connections, but never their rooms.
                    The same fort, different access levels.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Overlays -->
        <section id="overlays" class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">Overlays</span>
                <h2>Same floor plan, <em>different lenses</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    Architects have used transparent overlay sheets for centuries &mdash; structural, electrical,
                    plumbing, HVAC on the same blueprint. RuneFort does the same for cognitive systems.
                </p>

                <div class="overlay-grid">
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">&mdash;</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Structure</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">Rooms, walls, corridors, gates, towers. Always on.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">F</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Flow</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">Animated arrows showing data and token movement through phases.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">T</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Thermal</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">Activity heatmap. Hot rooms are busy, cold rooms are dormant.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">P</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Temporal</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">PULSE timing. Which rooms are in which phase right now.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">D</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Diagnostic</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">PRISM scores, anomaly markers, failure clusters.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">R</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Rune</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">The dark code. Operation configs, policy rules, causal chains.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">C</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Confidence</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">Node confidence heatmap. Bright is high, dim is low.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overlay-card">
                        <div class="overlay-key">K</div>
                        <div class="overlay-name">Topology</div>
                        <div class="overlay-desc">SCC highlighting, kappa values, cycle visualization.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Components -->
        <section id="components" class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">9 Primitives</span>
                <h2>One tile composes <em>into anything</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    The Minecraft constraint: everything is made of the same primitive. A room is tiles with shared borders.
                    A corridor is tiles in a line. A tower is tiles that stack. No special-case rendering.
                </p>

                <table class="component-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Component</th>
                            <th>Fort Role</th>
                            <th>Composition</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneTile&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Any single cell</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Atomic &mdash; the primitive</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneRoom&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">A cognitive domain</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Bordered tile group</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneHall&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">A data flow path</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Linear tile sequence</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneTower&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Observation point</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Vertically stacked tiles</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneGate&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Router or checkpoint</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Tile with filter state</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneWall&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Policy boundary</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Barrier tile sequence</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneFort&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">One cognitive system</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Root container (fractal &mdash; forts nest inside rooms)</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneBridge&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Inter-system exchange</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Fort-to-fort connection</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td class="comp-name">&lt;RuneDistrict&gt;</td>
                            <td class="comp-role">Full ecosystem view</td>
                            <td class="comp-rule">Multi-fort layout</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Runes -->
        <section id="runes" class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">The Rune Layer</span>
                <h2>Hidden machinery <em>inside the walls</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    Runes are the machine language. The blueprint is the human language.
                    The fort should be immediately legible to anyone &mdash; &ldquo;that's a room, that's a hallway,
                    that's a locked door.&rdquo; Runes reward deeper inspection but never gatekeep understanding.
                </p>

                <div class="pillar-grid">
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1.2rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em;">бҡІбҡЁбҡ </div>
                        <h3>Fast Path</h3>
                        <p>
                            Retrieve &rarr; Route &rarr; Act. The standard execution path through a fort.
                            No deliberation needed, knowledge flows directly to action.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1.2rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em;">бҡІбҡЁбҡұбҡ </div>
                        <h3>Deliberation Path</h3>
                        <p>
                            When &kappa; &gt; 0, cyclic knowledge triggers deliberation.
                            The corridor pulses. Evidence is weighed. Only then: action.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1.2rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em;">бҡәбӣүбӣ—</div>
                        <h3>Escalation Path</h3>
                        <p>
                            Disruption detected &rarr; diagnostic shielding &rarr; human escalation.
                            The tower fires. Someone gets paged.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="fort-diagram" style="text-align: center; white-space: normal; line-height: 2.5; font-size: 1rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; padding: 2.5rem;">
                    <span class="room" title="Kaunan вҖ” torch/knowledge вҖ” retrieve">бҡІ</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Ansuz вҖ” signal вҖ” route">бҡЁ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Fehu вҖ” wealth/store вҖ” act">бҡ </span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Jera вҖ” harvest вҖ” learn">бӣғ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Dagaz вҖ” dawn вҖ” consolidate">бӣһ</span>
                    &ensp;
                    <span class="rune" title="Algiz вҖ” protection вҖ” PRISM">бӣү</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Raidho вҖ” journey вҖ” deliberation">бҡұ</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Tiwaz вҖ” justice вҖ” governance">бӣҸ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Sowilo вҖ” sun вҖ” PULSE cadence">бӣҠ</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Perthro вҖ” mystery вҖ” epistemic frontier">бӣҲ</span>
                    &ensp;
                    <span class="room" title="Thurisaz вҖ” thorn вҖ” access denial">бҡҰ</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Uruz вҖ” strength вҖ” edge weight">бҡў</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Gebo вҖ” gift вҖ” bridge token">бҡ·</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Wunjo вҖ” harmony вҖ” consensus">бҡ№</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Haglaz вҖ” disruption вҖ” anomaly">бҡә</span>
                    &ensp;
                    <span class="rune" title="Naudiz вҖ” constraint вҖ” boundary">бҡҫ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Isa вҖ” ice вҖ” sealed memory">бӣҒ</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Eihwaz вҖ” endurance вҖ” glacial">бӣҮ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Berkanan вҖ” growth вҖ” promotion">бӣ’</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Ehwaz вҖ” movement вҖ” data flow">бӣ–</span>
                    &ensp;
                    <span class="room" title="Mannaz вҖ” human вҖ” escalation">бӣ—</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Laguz вҖ” water вҖ” stream processing">бӣҡ</span>
                    <span class="room" title="Ingwaz вҖ” seed вҖ” goal node">бӣң</span>
                    <span class="rune" title="Othala вҖ” heritage вҖ” workspace root">бӣҹ</span>
                    <br />
                    <span style="font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--dim);">24 Elder Futhark runes &mdash; hover for meanings</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Ecosystem -->
        <section id="ecosystem" class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">Ecosystem</span>
                <h2>Every product gets <em>a fort</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    Every product in the [&] ecosystem maps to a fort. The layout is generated from
                    PULSE loop manifests, [&] capability bindings, and Supabase schemas. If it declares a loop, it gets a fort.
                </p>

                <div class="eco-grid">
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бҡІбҡЁбҡ бӣғбӣһ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">Graphonomous</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Memory substrate. Nested in every fort.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣҸ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">Delegatic</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Governance. Its walls are every fort's walls.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣҡ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">TickTickClock</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Temporal intelligence. The district clocktower.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бҡ№</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">AgenTroMatic</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Multi-agent orchestration. 7-phase deliberation.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бҡұ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">Deliberatic</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Argumentation protocol. Merkle-chained evidence.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣү</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">PRISM</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Diagnostic watchtower. 9 CL dimensions.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бҡ </span>
                        <div class="eco-name">WebHost.Systems</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Hosting layer. Deploy and invoke agents.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣң</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">Agentelic</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Engineering. Spec-driven build pipeline.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бҡ·</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">FleetPrompt</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Marketplace. Trust-scored agent registry.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣҠ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">BendScript</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Knowledge editor. Canvas-based graph UI.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣҲ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">GeoFleetic</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Spatial intelligence. Federated fleet learning.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eco-card">
                        <span class="eco-rune">бӣҹ</span>
                        <div class="eco-name">SpecPrompt</div>
                        <div class="eco-role">Standards. Git-based spec lifecycle.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Not a Dashboard -->
        <section class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">Why Not a Dashboard</span>
                <h2>Blueprints scale.<br /><em>Dashboards don't.</em></h2>
                <p class="lead">
                    Blueprints were literally invented to represent massive buildings and remain navigable.
                    Dungeon maps become mazes. Isometric views become visual noise. Dashboards run out of panels.
                    Blueprints handle campus &rarr; room &rarr; detail with the same visual language.
                </p>

                <div class="dark-factory-split">
                    <div class="df-card dark">
                        <h3>Current observability</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Flat dashboards with panels that multiply</li>
                            <li>Trace waterfalls that require expertise to read</li>
                            <li>Abstract DAG visualizations disconnected from runtime</li>
                            <li>No spatial intuition for non-engineers</li>
                            <li>Auditors, PMs, and stakeholders locked out</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="df-card lit">
                        <h3>Spatial cognition</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бҡІ</span> Walk through the system, don't scan a spreadsheet</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣҠ</span> Overlay system &mdash; one map, multiple lenses</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣһ</span> Same tile grid from district to single operation</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бӣ—</span> Immediately legible to anyone, runes reward depth</li>
                            <li><span class="rune-glyph">бҡ·</span> B2B boundaries built into the visual model</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="pullquote">
                    <p>
                        The fort is alive. Rooms brighten with activity and dim with decay.
                        Corridors pulse during deliberation. Walls thicken when policies block.
                        Towers fire when anomalies hit. The fort breathes with your system.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Tech -->
        <section class="section-border">
            <div class="container">
                <span class="section-label">Stack</span>
                <h2>Built with <em>what works</em></h2>

                <div class="pillar-grid">
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1rem;">&#9638;</div>
                        <h3>SvelteKit + CSS Grid</h3>
                        <p>
                            Zero-dependency rendering. SVG overlays. SSR-compatible and accessible.
                            Pan and zoom in ~20 lines of JS. Cloudflare Pages for zero-cost hosting.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1rem;">&#8693;</div>
                        <h3>MCP Data Sources</h3>
                        <p>
                            Live data from Graphonomous MCP and PRISM MCP.
                            PULSE manifests parsed at build time for fort skeletons.
                            RuneFort never makes LLM calls &mdash; pure visualization.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pillar">
                        <div class="pillar-icon" style="font-size: 1rem;">&#8634;</div>
                        <h3>Its Own Loop</h3>
                        <p>
                            RuneFort learns from how you navigate. Frequently visited rooms
                            move closer. Unused rooms recede. The fort is itself
                            a continual learning system.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <section class="section-border" style="text-align: center; padding: 6rem 0;">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Your autonomous workflows<br />deserve <em>a control room</em></h2>
                <p class="lead" style="margin: 1.5rem auto 2.5rem; text-align: center;">
                    Whether you're running a dark factory, orchestrating multi-agent workflows,
                    or building the next cognitive architecture &mdash; if it has a loop, it gets a fort.
                </p>
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
